# dunst.dcol — no-op override
# Placed in ~/.config/wallbash/always/ to shadow the HyDE-owned version in
# ~/.local/share/wallbash/always/dunst.dcol which calls dunst.sh and tries
# to restart dunst. Since we use swaync, dunst is not installed and that
# script fires an error notification on every startup and theme switch.
# This empty dcol prevents that by taking priority over the HyDE version.
# Output path is /dev/null so wallbash has a valid target but writes nothing.
/dev/null
